Deviating from the main line. Black typically plays 6.... 0-0 7. Bd3 Nbd7 8. Nge2 Re8 9. 0-0 c6 10. Qc2 Nf8 11. f3. However, this usually favors White because he has two possible pawn breaks: A minority attack on c6 and a break on e4. While Black has much trouble with a c5 break.
